1PP 5737-L11 IBM COBOL for Linux                     1.2.0      TINYJOIN  Date 06/13/2026  Time 19:50:20   Page     2               
   LineID  PL SL  ----+-*A-1-B--+----2----+----3----+----4----+----5----+----6----+----7-|--+----8 Map and Cross Reference           
0  000001                IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.                                                 |                                  
   000002                PROGRAM-ID.    TINYJOIN.                                                 |                                  
   000003                AUTHOR.        FRASER.                                                   |                                  
   000004               ******************************************************************        |                                  
   000005               * Program     : TINYJOIN.CBL                                              |                                  
   000006               * Application : Tiny Pointers lab -- COBOL hash-join demo                 |                                  
   000007               * Type        : Batch COBOL Program                                       |                                  
   000008               * Function    : A relational JOIN of two flat files using the             |                                  
   000009               *               "load-balancing dereference table" of                     |                                  
   000010               *               Tiny Pointers (arXiv:2111.12800, Section 3).              |                                  
   000011               *                                                                         |                                  
   000012               *   Tables : CUSTOMER.DAT (inner / build) joined to                       |                                  
   000013               *            ORDERS.DAT   (outer / probe) on customer id.                 |                                  
   000014               *                                                                         |                                  
   000015               *   The dereference table hashes a key to a BUCKET of B slots and         |                                  
   000016               *   stores it in any free slot j.  The "tiny pointer" is just j --        |                                  
   000017               *   ceil(log2 B) bits -- not a full record pointer.  A few buckets        |                                  
   000018               *   fill up (the paper's delta-fraction); those spill to a small          |                                  
   000019               *   linear-probe OVERFLOW region (the paper's backup table) so the        |                                  
   000020               *   join is LOSSLESS.  DEREFERENCE = recompute bucket from the key,       |                                  
   000021               *   scan <= B slots: a bounded, tail-free probe even at high load.        |                                  
   000022               *                                                                         |                                  
   000023               *   This is a CPU, single-thread teaching demo: the point is the          |                                  
   000024               *   STRUCTURE, the DENSITY it reaches, and the tiny HANDLE width --       |                                  
   000025               *   not raw speed (that is the CUDA Fortran engine next door).            |                                  
   000026               ******************************************************************        |                                  
   000027                ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.                                                    |                                  
   000028                INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.                                                    |                                  
   000029                FILE-CONTROL.                                                            |                                  
   000030                    SELECT CUSTOMER-FILE                                                 |48                                
   000031                        ASSIGN TO 'data/CUSTOMER.DAT'                                    |                                  
   000032                        ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL                                  |                                  
   000033                        FILE STATUS IS CUST-STATUS.                                      |97                                
   000034                                                                                         |                                  
   000035                    SELECT ORDERS-FILE                                                   |53                                
   000036                        ASSIGN TO 'data/ORDERS.DAT'                                      |                                  
   000037                        ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL                                  |                                  
   000038                        FILE STATUS IS ORD-STATUS.                                       |100                               
   000039                                                                                         |                                  
   000040                    SELECT JOINED-FILE                                                   |59                                
   000041                        ASSIGN TO 'data/JOINED.DAT'                                      |                                  
   000042                        ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL                                  |                                  
   000043                        FILE STATUS IS JN-STATUS.                                        |103                               
   000044                                                                                         |                                  
   000045                DATA DIVISION.                                                           |                                  
   000046                FILE SECTION.                                                            |                                  
   000047                                                                                         |                                  
   000048                FD  CUSTOMER-FILE.                                                       |                                  
   000049                01  CUST-REC.                                                            |                                  
   000050                    05  CR-ID            PIC 9(6).                                       |                                  
   000051                    05  CR-NAME          PIC X(20).                                      |                                  
   000052                                                                                         |                                  
   000053                FD  ORDERS-FILE.                                                         |                                  
   000054                01  ORD-REC.                                                             |                                  
   000055                    05  OR-ID            PIC 9(8).                                       |                                  
   000056                    05  OR-CID           PIC 9(6).                                       |                                  
   000057                    05  OR-AMT           PIC 9(9).                                       |                                  
